com.kuka.time

Class StatisticTimer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.time.StatisticTimer

  • public final class StatisticTimer
extends Object
    Usage of the Statistic Timer for periodic cyclic timing measurements. Typical operation: 
     
 // Create an instance of the timer itself
 StatisticTimer timer = new StatisticTimer();
 
 // Sample one timestep - begin time measurement
 OneTimeStep step = operationStats.newTimeStep();
 
 // Perform your computational heavy load routine
 // doTheOperation();
 
 // End time measurement
 step.end();
 
 // ...
 
 // Print current statistics
 System.out.println(timer);

        public StatisticTimer(int nCallsInit,
                      long minTimeInit,
                      long maxTimeInit,
                      double meanInit,
                      double m2Init)
        Creates a new instance of StatisticTimer with initial conditions to reinitialize statistics.
        Parameters:
        nCallsInit - number of measurements performed.
        minTimeInit - minimum time recorded among all the measurements
        maxTimeInit - maximum time recorded among all the measurements
        meanInit - current mean of all the measurements performed
        m2Init - sum of squares of differences from the current mean
